{
  "texts": [
    "• Evaluator: We evaluate each beam candidate beam i extended from the template temp (t-1) i by calculating the target losses mentioned in Section 3.1 on the victim model π.",
    "The target loss function is denoted as L, and the target losses for each attack candidate in beam i can be represented as:",
    "• Selector: We merge the beams of candidates generated previously, S = ∪ i beam i and their associated losses, L = ∪ i ℓ i.",
    "Finally, we update the adversarial candidates Q with those having the minimum losses:",
    "At the end of the optimization loop, the suffix with the minimum loss from Q is selected as the optimal jailbreak prompt."
  ]
}